#IFNDEF USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET
SVRF MESSAGE "USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option is off in this DRC run."
SVRF MESSAGE "1. It will use low voltage space rules to do DRC, as you do not assign the voltage marker & the net connects to IO MOS and core MOS simultaneousely"
SVRF MESSAGE "2. If the designer knows some nets use high volatage, please turn on USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option to check high voltage space rules conservatively." 
SVRF MESSAGE "3. If you turn on USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option, you might find some high voltage space violations are actually false errors because these nets actually use low voltage. You can turn off the option."
SVRF MESSAGE "4. It is strongly recommended to assign volatage marker layer on the nets connect to IO MOS and core MOS simultaneousely." 
SVRF MESSAGE "5. This warning is just a reminder, not a gated item for tape-out."
   
IO_CONNECT_CORE_NET_VOLTAGE_IS_CORE:WARNING1 { @ USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option is off in this DRC run.
@ 1. It will use low voltage space rules to do DRC, as you do not assign the voltage marker & the net connects to IO MOS and core MOS simultaneousely
@ 2. If the designer knows some nets use high volatage,
@    please turn on USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option to check high voltage space rules conservatively. 
@ 3. If you turn on USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET option, you might find some high voltage space violations are actually false errors
@    because these nets actually use low voltage. You can turn off the option.
@ 4. It is strongly recommended to assign volatage marker layer on the nets connect to IO MOS and core MOS simultaneousely. 
@ 5. This warning is just a reminder, not a gated item for tape-out.
    COPY CHIPx 
}
#ENDIF


